body:
Concept ACK. This matches the change that was [backported to the 5.12 branch](https://codereview.qt-project.org/c/qt%2Fqtbase/+/322507) (`git branch --contains c5d904639dbd690a36306e2b455610029704d821`. We don't have it, because a 5.12.11 release has not been tagged (yet); it should happen  in the first half of this year, according to https://wiki.qt.io/Qt_5.12_Release.

Similar to other Qt patches we have, can you add a note at the top of the patch file, mentioning that this can be dropped when using Qt 5.12.11 or later.

@jarolrod or @Sjors could either of you test a depends build and confirm that `bitcoin-qt` run on macOS 11.
